The paper focuses on the extraction of event-centric document collections from large scale web archives, which involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.DL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of specialized focused extraction algorithm, which falls under the category of information extraction (IE) and text mining. Hence, cs.CL is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential applications of the proposed method in social sciences, historical sciences, and journalism, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
